text: I’m in my early 20’s and been suffering with wanting to be dead for years, hoping on day I’m speeding in my car I just lose control and crash so it looks like a accident
I’m so tired, I don’t understand how people live and work till they die

I’m already just smooching off my parents and living in there basement doing nothing with my life, well I do tons of things like I said I got some good hobby’s to keep me busy but nothing entertains me, I just rather be dead so I don’t have to do anything
I just want to be loved
I want anything but how I feel right now
every single time when I see articles about people committing suicide, I feel envious
I do not have the following;- family- friends- pets- a job- schoolingAnything I enjoy doing, is not worth the lifetime of pain and suffering
There is not one thing that can make it worth living, even if I enjoy it a lot
There will not be one thing that will give me 80+ years of brain chemicals to make me happy
